  "title": "windowTitle does not trigger when page loads",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for participating in this project! We will try to answer as soon as possible 🙏\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\nThe `windowTitle` option for routing does not trigger when the page first loads.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\nThis issue can be easily reproduced via official SEO friendly URLs demo\r\n\r\n1. Open demo via [CodeSandbox](https://codesandbox.io/s/github/algolia/doc-code-samples/tree/master/InstantSearch.js/routing-seo-friendly)\r\n2. Run the demo and click \"Open in New Window\"\r\n3. Type something to search, notice the title change\r\n4. Refresh the page using browser reload.\r\n5. Title does not change.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior 💭**\r\nThe page title should contains correct queries from `windowTitle` after page reload.\r\n\r\n**Screencast 🎬**\r\nhttps://www.useloom.com/share/96c3c8f3329041c7bc6d74e232812ad4\r\n\r\n**Environment:**\r\n - OS: macOS\r\n - Browser: Google Chrome\r\n - Version: 73.0.3683.86\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nAdd any other context about the problem here.\r\n",
